    ),
    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# Grok Feature Usage, MAU Penetration, and AI Customer Counts\n\n## MAU Penetration and Grok Feature Usage\n\nThe filing discloses the following user metrics as of March 31, 2026:\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| **Supported accounts (LTM)** | Over 1.3 billion (up from over 1.1 billion as of Dec 31, 2025) |\n| **Combined MAUs (Grok + X)** | ~550 million (up from ~520 million as of Dec 31, 2025) |\n| **MAUs using Grok\'s AI features** | ~117 million |\n| **Daily posts on X** | ~350 million |\n\n**Grok feature penetration rate**: Approximately **21.3%** of combined MAUs (117M / 550M) actively used Grok\'s AI features.\n\n### MAU Methodology\nThe filing defines MAU as users who interacted with Grok or X via web browsers or mobile apps at least once during a 30-day period. Key methodological notes:\n- Users accessing **both** Grok and X are identified via sign-in traffic to avoid double-counting\n- Only **registered** X or Grok account holders are included\n- The company tracks the subset of users who used Grok\'s AI features versus those who have not, based on the source of server requests\n- Reported MAU is acknowledged as an **estimate** that may not fully capture all duplication\n\n### Strategic Posture on MAUs\nThe filing explicitly states that while MAUs provide a measure of user base size and engagement, the company is **"focused on revenue and operating margin"** and manages the business with the objective of driving sustainable revenue growth and profitability **"rather than with the primary objective of growing or maintaining MAU levels."**\n\n---\n\n## Grok Product Usage Metrics\n\n### Imagine (Image & Video Generation)\n- **~10 billion images** produced per month on average\n- **~2 billion videos** produced per month on average\n- For the quarter ending March 31, 2026\n- Current video iteration supports up to 15 seconds at 720p\n\n### Grok Voice\n- Developed in under six months\n- Real-time speech engine with multilingual performance\n\n### Grok Chat\n- Primary conversational interface available via grok.com, dedicated mobile apps, X platform integration, and the xAI API\n- Supports text/voice queries, web search, X data integration, code execution, and multimodal analysis\n\n### Model Performance\n- Grok achieved frontier-level performance in scientific reasoning (GPQA Diamond score) within two years of its initial model release\n- Roadmap includes multi-trillion parameter models representing a potential step change in reasoning depth\n\n---\n\n## AI Customer Counts and Subscriptions\n\n### Paid Subscriber Base (as of March 31, 2026)\n\n| Subscription Category | Paid Subscribers |\n|----------------------|-----------------|\n| **X Premium and Premium+** | ~4.4 million |\n| **SuperGrok, SuperGrok Heavy, and SuperGrok Lite** | ~1.9 million |\n| **Total Active Paid Subscribers** | **~6.3 million** |\n\n### Grok Subscription Tiers\nThe filing lists the following Grok subscription offerings:\n- **Basic**\n- **SuperGrok**\n- **SuperGrok Heavy**\n- **SuperGrok Lite**\n\nEach is priced on a monthly or annual basis, with higher tiers unlocking expanded model access, increased usage limits, priority compute, and premium features for power users and enterprise-grade applications.\n\n### Enterprise and Government AI Offerings\nThe company has launched four distinct enterprise/government products:\n\n1. **Grok Business** — Subscription-based offering for internal business applications and workflows\n2. **Grok Enterprise** — Subscription-based offering designed for enterprise deployment with customized workflows and security needs\n3. **Grok API** — Application programming interface enabling developers to integrate Grok models into external software\n4. **xAI Gov** — Government-focused AI offering\n\nEnterprise products are sold on **license-, consumption-, or outcome-based pricing models**.\n\n### Strategic Partnerships\n- Partnering with **Cursor** to advance Grok and potentially create jointly-owned coding and knowledge work AI models trained on SpaceX\'s compute infrastructure\n- Tesla\'s January 2026 investment in xAI (converted to SpaceX equity upon acquisition) underpins collaborative development of **Macrohard** (agentic AI platform) and **Terafab** (AI chip manufacturing)\n\n---\n\n## Market Opportunity Sizing\n\n### Consumer AI Subscriptions\n- **Estimated market opportunity: ~$760 billion annually**\n- Methodology: Global population aged 10+ in 2025 (~5.5 billion per Euromonitor) × weighted average monthly subscription revenue of $12\n- Weighted average assumes:\n  - $30/month for SuperGrok in high-income countries\n  - $8/month in upper-middle and lower-middle income countries\n  - Significantly lower in low-income countries (per World Bank definitions)\n\n### Digital Advertising\n- Global digital advertising spending totaled **$600 billion in 2025** (per S&P Global Market Intelligence)\n- X positions itself to capture share through AI-driven performance marketing tools and Grok integration\n\n---\n\n## Distribution of AI Features Through X\n\nThe filing emphasizes that Grok\'s integration with X is a **core competitive differentiator**:\n\n- Grok holds **"front and center real estate"** on the X platform with a prominent Grok icon\n- Native integration delivers personalized feeds, smarter recommendations, and low-latency AI assistance\n- X Premium tiers (Basic, Premium, Premium+) offer expanded features, ad-reduced experiences, and **priority Grok interactions**\n- Grok\'s chat functionality was integrated into the X app in 2023\n- Public X data enhances Grok\'s training and reasoning capabilities\n- The company intends to **further embed Grok throughout the platform** to enhance discovery, post analysis, user support, and personalization\n- An incremental monetization opportunity is identified through **introducing advertising into the stand-alone Grok offering**\n\n### "Spicy" and "Unhinged" Modes\nThe filing discloses risk factors associated with less constrained AI features:\n- **"Spicy" Imagine Mode** — generates more candid, irreverent image outputs\n- **"Unhinged" Voice Mode** — generates harsher, less reserved voice outputs\n\nThese modes present heightened risks including reputational harm, potentially explicit content, misinformation, intellectual property infringement, and increased regulatory scrutiny.',
